<subSubSection lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="475" pageId="29" pageNumber="474" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="29.[826,1443,1607,1905]" lastBlockId="30.[142,758,195,401]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="475" pageId="29" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis box="[826,927,1607,1628]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="474">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="COSTA" authorityYear="1844" box="[943,1086,1607,1628]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Periclimenes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="29" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[943,1086,1607,1628]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="474">Periclimenes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a speciose genus; 
<bibRefCitation author="Okuno J &amp; Mitsuhashi M" pageId="29" pageNumber="474" pagination="487 - 496" refId="ref73749" refString="Okuno J, Mitsuhashi M. 2003. A new species of Periclimenes Costa, 1844 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Palaemonidae) from the Ryukyu Islands, southern Japan. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 116 (2): 487 - 496." type="journal article" year="2003">Okuno &amp; Mitsuhashi (2003)</bibRefCitation>
considered the genus to include 174 valid nominal species, most of which are commensal with scleractinian corals or their associated invertebrates, and a few of which are now known from deep (more than 
<quantity box="[961,1032,1761,1782]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="29" pageNumber="474" unit="m" value="100.0">100 m</quantity>
) waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Hayashi K-I &amp; Ohtomi J" box="[1140,1431,1761,1783]" pageId="29" pageNumber="474" pagination="160 - 171" refId="ref67475" refString="Hayashi K-I, Ohtomi J. 2001. A new species of the genus Periclimenes (Decapoda: Caridea: Palaemonidae) collected from hydrothermal vent fields in Kagoshima Bay, Japan. Crustacean Research 30: 160 - 171." type="journal article" year="2001">Hayashi &amp; Ohtomi, 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The genus is largely circumtropical, and, although most records are for specimens collected in relatively shallow waters, the genus has been found as deep as 
<quantity box="[826,910,1883,1905]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.285" pageId="29" pageNumber="474" unit="m" value="1285.0">1285 m</quantity>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Chace FA Jr &amp; Bruce AJ" box="[977,1231,1883,1905]" pageId="29" pageNumber="474" pagination="1 - 152" refId="ref62850" refString="Chace FA Jr, Bruce AJ. 1993. The caridean shrimps (Crustacea: Decapoda) of the Albatross Philippine Expedition, 1907 - 1910, part 6: superfamily Palaemonoidea. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 543: 1 - 152." type="journal article" year="1993">Chace &amp; Bruce, 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poore GCB" box="[1247,1429,1883,1905]" pageId="29" pageNumber="474" refId="ref74874" refString="Poore GCB. 2004. Marine decapod Crustacea of southern Australia: A guide to identification. Melbourne: CSIRO Publishing." type="book" year="2004">Poore, 2004: 95</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Bergquist DC &amp; Ward T &amp; Cordes EE &amp; McNelis T &amp; Kosoff R &amp; Hourdez S &amp; Carney R &amp; Fisher CR" box="[142,400,195,217]" pageId="30" pageNumber="475" pagination="197 - 222" refId="ref61298" refString="Bergquist DC, Ward T, Cordes EE, McNelis T, Kosoff R, Hourdez S, Carney R, Fisher CR. 2003. Community structure of vestimentiferan-generated habitat islands from upper Louisiana slope cold seeps. Journal of Experimental Marine Biology and Ecology 289 (2): 197 - 222." type="journal article" year="2003">
Bergquist 
<emphasis box="[263,319,195,217]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="475">et al.</emphasis>
(2003)
</bibRefCitation>
listed, in an appendix, several decapod taxa from the Bush Hill and GC234 sites (cold seeps) in the northern Gulf of Mexico, and included ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[147,331,287,308]" class="Malacostraca" family="Palaemonidae" genus="Periclimenes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="475" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[147,290,287,308]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="475">Periclimenes</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
’ among the taxa observed. No specimens were collected. To date, only one nominal species of this genus is known from hydrothermal vents off 
<collectingCountry box="[142,212,380,401]" name="Japan" pageId="30" pageNumber="475">Japan</collectingCountry>
(see below).
</paragraph>
